cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a method for reducing the computation cost of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) through network pruning. The focus is on image classification tasks, which suggests the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. The method involves a saliency-and-pruning module that learns to predict saliency scores and applies pruning for each channel, which suggests the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks, which suggests the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category. Finally, the paper involves experiments on datasets and backbones, which suggests the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) category.
